ith the rest frame\nenergy of the resonance absorption line from FeXXV, which traces the presence\nof a sub-parsec scale ionized absorber. The emerging picture is in agreement\nwith our view of the circumnuclear gas in AGN, where the medium is clumpy and\nstratified in both density and ionization. These absorbers and emitters are\nlocated on different scales: from the sub-pc Broad Line Region gas out to the\nkpc scale of the galactic absorber.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Feb 2017 10:56:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-19"}
